# Stellar ZK Hackathon

Before building on Stellar, read [skills.stellar.org](https://skills.stellar.org/) for current best practices.

## ZK and privacy work

- Use the **zk-proofs** skill for Groth16 verifiers, BLS12-381, BN254/Poseidon, Noir, RISC Zero, privacy pools, and confidential tokens.
- Always verify CAP status, target network protocol version, and `soroban-sdk` host-function support before relying on ZK primitives.
- Treat BN254 and Poseidon as status-sensitive (CAP-0074/0075); confirm availability on the target network.

## Contract development

- Prefer OpenZeppelin Stellar patterns for Soroban contracts (`setup-stellar-contracts`, `upgrade-stellar-contracts`, `develop-secure-contracts`).
- Use the OpenZeppelin Contracts MCP server when generating fungible, stablecoin, or NFT contracts.

## Documentation

- Reference [docs/llms.txt](docs/llms.txt) for Stellar developer documentation navigation.
